Switch to gnu17, a GCC bug-fix version of the C11 standard.

What is C17 and what changes have been made to the language?
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47529854/

Signed-off-by: Mario Roy <...>

Curated patches from ZEN/XanMod/SUNLIGHT

ZEN: INTERACTIVE: Tune ondemand governor for interactivity
ZEN: dm-crypt: Disable workqueues for crypto ops
XANMOD: block/mq-deadline: Increase write priority, disable front_merges
XANMOD: block: Set rq_affinity to force complete I/O on same CPU
XANMOD: blk-wbt: Set wbt_default_latency_nsec() to 2msec
XANMOD: vfs: Decrease rate at which vfs caches are reclaimed
XANMOD: lib/kconfig.debug: disable default SYMBOLIC_ERRNAME and DEBUG_BUGVERBOSE
SUNLIGHT: x86/tsc: Use rdtsc_ordered() when RDTSCP or LFENCE_RDTSC are supported
SUNLIGHT: processor_idle: Skip dummy wait for Zen microarchitecture
Revert sched: update rq->avg_idle when a task is moved to an idle CPU
Revert tcp: give up on stronger sk_rcvbuf checks (for now)
Add Logitech C310 USB quirk
Speed up zstd compression
sched/fair: Add sched_smt_active check for fastpaths
sched: Unify SMT active check via sched_smt_active()
sched/fair: use rq_clock() in update_tg_load_avg() rate-limit
sched/fair: Rebuild load weight when switching to fair

